column5: http://www.ustream.tv/channel/shiocton3  Anybody seen this before? Cool underwater live camera in Wisconsin, watching the walleye going up stream to spawn. Every so often you'll see a group of em passing by. Pretty cool I think.
I look forward to watching it every year, thanks for posting it!
Every year that wolf river cam gets me in the mood.

There is another awesome river cam at the st.marys river dam in the sault st Marie on the Edison power gen station on the United States side it's awesome u can see all types of fish atlantics browns sturgeons and walleyes !!!!!!! Try to show the link ??? I'm on my phone I cant

Locnar I do not want mean to take away from your thread but seeing as it is related could may just a couple of members give their views if they have an underwater camera do they get enough enjoyment out of it for the price, maybe put it under a new thread, thanks again.

I've thought about getting one... but they are damn pricey. Plus I'd rather have the ability to leave one in the water to be able to watch when I'm not there to see what kind of activity is in that certain area of the water... but that would be a pricey and risky thing to do, don't want anyone walking away with it
never saw this before but just saw 2 tanks wonder on by - road trip anyone ?

I had a fish tv, it broke, replaced it with a cabelas color LCD, got stolen, replaced with aqua vu now, and they discontinued the one i have.. just cant win.  On the bright side, I would do it all again in a heartbeat, i would just drop the big bucks in the first place. I learned an insane amount from my aquavu.
Damn stubbed my toe... no night light!  G
Watched it on and off all day at work , a whole lot of Whitefish , 2 Sturgeon a Rock Bass , 20 or so Suckers and at least 100 Walleye and a BIG Pike " Cam #2"
